==Translingual==

===Symbol===
'''α'''
# The [[lower case]] letter [[alpha]], the first letter of the modern [[Greek alphabet]].
# The [[fine structure constant]].
# {{math}} {{physics}} Represents [[angular acceleration]].
# Used in [[chemical nomenclature]].
# {{star}} Used to identify the brightest [[star]] in a [[constellation]] (eg [[α-Centaur]]).
# Used in marking scheme: α, β, γ or α+, α, α-, β etc.

'''α''''
# The number one in [[w:Greek numerals|Greek numerals]].

''',α'''
# The number 1000 in Greek numerals.

====Related terms====
* [[alpha particle|α-particle]].
* [[α-naphthol]]
* [[α-Centauri]]

===Pronunciation===
# In modern Greek it represents the [[w:Open front unrounded vowel|[a]]] sound similar to the '''a''' in ''h'''a'''t'' and '''''A'''thens''.
# [[IPA]] /æ/ /ə/
# [[SAMPA]] /{/ /@/

